'''Swamp gas''' was a chemical weapon designed by [[Jenna Zan Arbor]] and used by the [[Confederacy of Independent Systems/Legends|Confederacy of Independent Systems]] against the [[Gungan/Legends|Gungans]] of [[Ohma-D'un/Legends|Ohma-D'un]]. Although it could kill Gungans in seconds, it took somewhat longer to kill members of other [[Species/Legends|species]]. It caused blistered skin and internal bleeding.

[[Obi-Wan Kenobi/Legends|Obi-Wan Kenobi]] recovered the antidote on a [[Mission to Queyta|mission]] to [[Queyta]] with [[Jedi Master/Legends|Jedi Masters]] [[Fay]], [[Nico Diath]], [[Knol Ven'nari]] and [[Jon Antilles]]. The [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] fought [[Asajj Ventress/Legends|Asajj Ventress]] and [[Durge/Legends|Durge]] for the antidote, though Obi-Wan alone survived to return to the [[Jedi Temple/Legends|Jedi Temple]].

As of [[20 BBY/Legends|20 BBY]], the [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Galactic Republic]] had enlisted the help of the [[Luurian Genetic Enclave]] to study the swamp gas antidote, and believed the threat of Separatist bioweapons was over&mdash;although the research on Queyta would lead to the creation of [[Trihexalophine1138]], the chemical weapon that devastated [[Honoghr/Legends|Honoghr]].

Swamp gas may have had links with [[Dioxis/Legends|dioxis]], the toxic gas commonly used by [[Neimoidian/Legends|Neimoidians]] to dispose of their enemies. On [[Cato Neimoidia/Legends|Cato Neimoidia]], Obi-Wan Kenobi identified a toxic gas emitted from [[Nute Gunray/Legends|Nute Gunray's]] [[Mechno-chair/Legends|mechno-chair]] as dioxis, though it was later verified as swamp gas by [[Captain/Legends|Captain]] [[Dyne]] of [[Republic Intelligence/Legends|Republic Intelligence]].

[[Mimban/Legends|Mimban]] produced a swamp gas that was rumored to be used by the [[Yuuzhan Vong]] in their [[Fire Breather]]s on [[Gyndine/Legends|Gyndine]].

==Behind the scenes==
Swamp gas may be based on [[Wikipedia:Mustard gas|mustard gas]], as it resembles it closely in its effects.

